org.gradoop.flink.model.impl.operators.exclusion

Class ReduceExclusion<G extends GraphHead,V extends Vertex,E extends Edge,LG extends BaseGraph<G,V,E,LG,GC>,GC extends BaseGraphCollection<G,V,E,LG,GC>>

  • java.lang.Object

    public class ReduceExclusion<G extends GraphHead,V extends Vertex,E extends Edge,LG extends BaseGraph<G,V,E,LG,GC>,GC extends BaseGraphCollection<G,V,E,LG,GC>>
extends Object
implements ReducibleBinaryBaseGraphToBaseGraphOperator<GC,LG>
    Computes the exclusion graph from a collection of logical graphs. Reduces the starting graph to contain only vertices and edges that are not contained in any other graph that is part of the given collection. The graph head of the starting graph is retained.

        public ReduceExclusion(GradoopId startId)
        Creates an operator instance which can be applied on a graph collection. As exclusion is not a commutative operation, a start graph needs to be set from which the remaining graphs will be excluded.
        Parameters:
        startId - graph id from which other graphs will be exluded from
